wdi2-SH.STA.POIS.P5.FE.def: Mortality rate attributed to unintentional poisonings is the number of female deaths from unintentional poisonings in a year per 100,000 female population.  Unintentional poisoning can be caused by household chemicals, pesticides, kerosene, carbon monoxide and medicines, or can be the result of environmental contamination or occupational chemical exposure.
wdi2-SH.STA.POIS.P5.FE.name: Mortality rate attributed to unintentional poisoning
wdi2-SH.STA.POIS.P5.FE.source: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository (http://apps.who.int/ghodata/).
